# 🎤 Interview Questions

### 1. What is OOP?

OOP is a programming paradigm based on objects and classes.

---

### 2. What are the four pillars of OOP?

* Encapsulation
* Inheritance
* Polymorphism
* Abstraction

---

### 3. Difference between Method Overloading and Overriding?

| Overloading          | Overriding      |
| -------------------- | --------------- |
| Same Class           | Parent & Child  |
| Compile Time         | Run Time        |
| Different Parameters | Same Parameters |

---

### 4. What is the difference between Abstract Class and Interface?

| Abstract Class        | Interface                |
| --------------------- | ------------------------ |
| Can have constructors | Cannot have constructors |
| Partial abstraction   | Full abstraction         |
| extends keyword       | implements keyword       |

---

### 5. What is Encapsulation?

Wrapping data and methods into a single class and restricting direct access.

